╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
Execute repair procedures on the reactor's corrupted configuration files
and automate the restoration process using shell scripts.

This sector contains three sub-missions:
    1. core/     - Fix corrupted config files with sed
    2. cooling/  - Batch operations with xargs
    3. scripts/  - Write and execute repair scripts

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

COMMAND REFERENCE:

    SED - Stream Editor:
    sed 's/old/new/' file          Replace first occurrence per line
    sed 's/old/new/g' file         Replace all occurrences
    sed -i '' 's/old/new/g' file   Edit file in place (macOS)
    sed -i 's/old/new/g' file      Edit file in place (Linux)
    sed '/pattern/d' file          Delete lines matching pattern

    XARGS - Build commands from input:
    echo "file1 file2" | xargs cat         Run cat on each file
    find . -name "*.txt" | xargs grep X    Search all found files
    ls *.cfg | xargs -I {} cp {} {}.bak    Copy with filename placeholder

    SHELL SCRIPTS:
    #!/bin/bash                    Shebang line
    chmod +x script.sh             Make executable
    ./script.sh                    Run script

